-- Brazil Prepares Measures to Lower Lending Rates, Folha Says
-- B y   R a y m o n d   C o l i t t
-- 2012-02-18T14:23:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-18/brazil-prepares-measures-to-lower-lending-rates-folha-says.html
Brazil ’s government is preparing
measures to lower the cost of credit toward helping the economy
grow by about 4 percent this year, Folha de S.Paulo reported,
citing unidentified advisers to President  Dilma Rousseff .  The proposals include tax breaks on lending and the use of
state-run banks to lower interest-rate spreads, the newspaper
said in its online edition today.  The  Finance Ministry  didn’t immediately respond to
telephone messages left seeking comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Raymond Colitt in Brasilia newsroom at 
 rcolitt@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 